repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The materials consists of pictures of individuals associated with Yale, including students, faculty, officers, and visitors. Includes portrait photographs, and prints of drawings and paintings.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: This collection differs from RU 686, Photographs of individuals from the Yale University News Bureau, which strictly contains photographs maintained by the university for publicity purposes.
Forms part of Yale Record Group 48-A (YRG 48-A), Yale pictorial records and collections.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Images of Yale Individuals (RU 684). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials consists of pictures of individuals associated with Yale, including students, faculty, officers, and visitors. Includes portrait photographs, and prints of drawings and paintings.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The images are arranged in two series and subsequent accessions. I. Alphabetical list of individuals. II. Oversize.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Accession 2015-A-056 is gift of George C. Anderheggen, 2015.
